               <msContents>
                  <summary>Gospel of John, ወንጌል፡ ዘዮሐንስ፡ Varia. F. i v: Asmat prayer against diarrhea. Notes. F. ii r: The book bears the seal of ownership (in blue ink) with an outer and inner line of text.  The outer line: "Abba Sawaros, archbishop of Southern Ethiopia and Echegge of Dabra Libanos. . . ."  The inner circle of text cites the text from John chapter 1: "Behold the lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world." There is also a note of ownership: "This gospel [of John] belongs to Abba ሣዊሮስ, archbishop of Southern Ethiopia which was given to him by his son and beloved Abba ገብረ መስቀል in 1923, Maggabit 20."  <locus target="#1r"/> mentions the scribe, እንግደሰው. <locus target="#99v"/> gives the baptismal name of the scribe, ወልደ መስቀል. <locus target="#99v"/> also contains a seal (in blue ink) of the Echegge, Gebre Masqal, "እጨጌ ገብ[ረ] መ[ስቀል]". <locus target="#100r"/>: Record: This gospel belongs to ሀብተ ሚካኤል, and was given to him by his father, Abba ገብረ ሕይወት. </summary>
